WEBVTT

00:00.643 --> 00:02.557
<i>Previously on</i> Mike & Molly...

00:02.558 --> 00:05.693
I remember when I was a little
girl working on my daddy's farm.

00:05.694 --> 00:07.028
Oh, please don't tell me
a story.

00:07.029 --> 00:08.195
Let me tell you a story.

00:08.197 --> 00:10.130
I was a meek little thing,

00:10.132 --> 00:13.201
scared of my own shadow
and the sheep I had to castrate.

00:13.202 --> 00:16.670
That's where you learned it?

00:16.672 --> 00:18.940
I had to pump my own water,
make my own clothes,

00:18.941 --> 00:21.441
and if the crop didn't get in,
well, we all went hungry.

00:21.443 --> 00:23.745
Just when I thought my life

00:23.746 --> 00:25.546
couldn't possibly get any worse,

00:25.547 --> 00:27.715
a city fella in a '56 Rambler

00:27.716 --> 00:31.119
pulled up to the house
and asked for directions.

00:31.120 --> 00:32.452
Was that Mike's dad?

00:32.454 --> 00:35.356
Hell no.
This was a real man.

00:35.357 --> 00:38.159
Wore a three-piece suit
with hard shoes

00:38.160 --> 00:42.497
and smelled like a pine forest
after a spring rain.

00:42.498 --> 00:44.365
That's very poetic, Peggy.

00:44.366 --> 00:45.800
What he did to me wasn't poetic.

00:45.801 --> 00:47.301
It was filthy.

00:47.302 --> 00:50.103
And I loved it.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

00:50.105 --> 00:52.006
Got to write it down. Go.

00:52.007 --> 00:53.940
MIKE:
<i>Look at you, writing again.</i>

00:53.942 --> 00:57.110
Yeah, a new story about
a young girl coming of age

00:57.112 --> 01:00.680
on a hardscrabble farm at the
base of the Mudlick Mountains.

01:00.682 --> 01:01.616
Mudlick? Th-That's weird.

01:01.617 --> 01:04.483
My mom grew up on a farm
in Mudlick.

01:06.955 --> 01:09.156
Aw, no!

01:12.594 --> 01:16.264
You know, we could write
about my playmates growing up.

01:16.265 --> 01:19.866
My best friend was a chicken.

01:19.868 --> 01:21.602
Named him George Hamilton

01:21.603 --> 01:23.805
on account
of he was just as handsome

01:23.806 --> 01:26.540
and just as brown.

01:26.542 --> 01:27.809
Sure.

01:27.810 --> 01:29.242
You know, a flightless bird

01:29.244 --> 01:31.645
is a wonderful pet for a child.

01:31.647 --> 01:33.648
That is unless your father
has a mean streak

01:33.649 --> 01:36.250
and a taste for cacciatore.

01:36.251 --> 01:38.118
What do you think of this dress?

01:38.120 --> 01:39.320
Oh, for God's sake.

01:39.321 --> 01:42.355
Can you not think about
that party for ten minutes?

01:42.357 --> 01:44.025
Oh, I'm sorry.
Do you get invited

01:44.026 --> 01:46.694
to big literary parties
every day? 'Cause I don't.

01:46.695 --> 01:48.762
Ah, who knows?
I don't get much mail

01:48.764 --> 01:51.966
since I accused the postman
of stealing the perfume cards

01:51.967 --> 01:54.334
out of my magazines.

01:55.270 --> 01:57.305
Where are you going?

01:57.306 --> 02:00.107
To try on this dress. We've done
enough work for the day.

02:00.108 --> 02:01.408
We haven't done a thing!

02:01.410 --> 02:04.110
Well, speak for yourself.
I found a dress.

02:08.183 --> 02:10.383
(buzzing)

02:11.119 --> 02:13.120
Keep buzzing, you bastards.

02:13.121 --> 02:15.089
Your reign of terror
is about to end.

02:15.090 --> 02:17.325
Don't tip 'em off.
Just smile and wave.

02:17.326 --> 02:19.927
Hello, wasps!
Just looking for the mail!

02:19.928 --> 02:21.394
All right,

02:21.396 --> 02:23.563
we got one chance
to torch their nest.

02:23.565 --> 02:26.366
You got to make sure
you keep that match lit.

02:26.368 --> 02:27.668
Hey, I got my end.

02:27.669 --> 02:29.403
You just worry about aiming
that Aqua Net.

02:29.404 --> 02:32.572
Are you sure you don't want
to call somebody?

02:32.574 --> 02:35.409
Or at least wait
for a third stooge?

02:35.410 --> 02:36.911
Nonsense. We got it.

02:36.912 --> 02:39.379
Besides, Carl was busy.

02:40.482 --> 02:42.749
(buzzing) (grunting, shouting)

02:47.356 --> 02:49.223
That's it.
I can't take it anymore.

02:49.224 --> 02:51.425
Just give 'em the porch.

02:51.426 --> 02:52.927
No. It ends today.

02:52.928 --> 02:55.196
You sting my bald head,
I burn down your house.

02:55.197 --> 02:57.631
It's the Chicago way.

02:57.633 --> 03:00.268
Wait a minute. Is that your
dress for the big party?

03:00.269 --> 03:02.202
Yeah, it is.
It's a little...

03:02.204 --> 03:03.771
a little flashy
for cocktail casual,

03:03.772 --> 03:05.873
but I thought, hey,
you only come up once,

03:05.874 --> 03:08.675
so they're gonna see
this up-and-comer coming.

03:08.677 --> 03:10.176
What-what party?

03:10.178 --> 03:12.713
Oh, it's nothing.
It's just a stuffy get-together

03:12.714 --> 03:15.283
with a bunch
of long-winded intellectuals.

03:15.284 --> 03:17.752
Ugh.
Exactly.

03:17.753 --> 03:20.153
I knew you'd hate it, and that's
why you don't have to go.

03:20.155 --> 03:21.354
Oh, no, I'm coming.

03:21.356 --> 03:23.624
No, Mike, seriously, you are...

03:23.625 --> 03:26.293
you are off the hook.

03:26.295 --> 03:27.595
Sweetie, I've been
married too long

03:27.596 --> 03:29.163
to fall for that one, all right?

03:29.164 --> 03:30.965
That's the old
"I don't need a birthday gift,"

03:30.966 --> 03:32.300
"Be honest about my haircut,"

03:32.301 --> 03:34.936
"Just tell me if you watch porn.
I don't care." Nah.

03:34.937 --> 03:37.438
No, sir. I will be at that party

03:37.439 --> 03:41.474
so you can show me off
to all your highbrow friends.

03:41.476 --> 03:44.045
Yeah. The-the thing is you
really don't need to do it...

03:44.046 --> 03:47.080
Bup, bup, bup, bup, bup, bup.
I am going, and that is that.

03:47.082 --> 03:48.382
You ready to do this?

03:48.383 --> 03:50.283
I was born ready.

03:51.119 --> 03:54.287
Joyce, get the door.

03:55.190 --> 03:57.324
Go! Go! Go!

03:57.326 --> 03:59.327
(buzzing)

03:59.328 --> 04:01.028
VINCE: Oop! My match went out!

04:01.029 --> 04:03.297
MIKE: Well, light another one!
My can's almost empty!

04:03.298 --> 04:04.799
VINCE: Too late! It was a setup!

04:04.800 --> 04:06.399
They knew we were coming!
Aah!

04:06.401 --> 04:07.768
God, they're all over me!

04:07.769 --> 04:09.536
Should we do something?

04:09.538 --> 04:11.204
You're right.
I'll get the camera.

