04:43.307 --> 04:45.274
Hey.
How's your patient?

04:45.275 --> 04:47.343
Well, for a guy
who swallowed three hornets,

04:47.344 --> 04:50.546
he's doing pretty good.

04:50.547 --> 04:52.181
Vince is a mess, too.

04:52.182 --> 04:54.849
I mean, we still
made love, but...

04:54.851 --> 04:58.487
oh, he was in a lot of pain.

04:58.488 --> 05:01.056
Really? Do we need to know that?

05:01.058 --> 05:01.924
You asked.

05:01.925 --> 05:04.427
Nobody asked.

05:04.428 --> 05:07.629
Is Mike still gonna be able
to go to your party? No.

05:07.631 --> 05:10.298
He says he is, but I'm gonna
encourage him to stay home.

05:10.300 --> 05:11.866
So he can rest?

05:12.703 --> 05:15.003
Sure.

05:15.005 --> 05:16.706
You don't want him to go.

05:16.707 --> 05:18.106
W... I didn't say that.

05:18.108 --> 05:19.342
Well, what are you saying?

05:19.343 --> 05:21.844
I'm saying that there's gonna be

05:21.845 --> 05:25.014
a bunch of stuffy,
overeducated intellectuals there

05:25.015 --> 05:27.650
and he's not gonna have anything
in common with them.

05:27.651 --> 05:28.817
Because he's dumb?

05:28.819 --> 05:30.619
No.

05:30.621 --> 05:32.887
Because you're afraid
he'll say something dumb.

05:33.724 --> 05:36.791
No.

05:37.928 --> 05:38.960
What?

05:38.962 --> 05:39.862
Seems very familiar,

05:39.863 --> 05:41.597
you not wanting your "family"

05:41.598 --> 05:43.498
to go to your events.

05:43.500 --> 05:47.002
Why-why did you air-quote
"family"?

05:47.004 --> 05:50.673
I'm sorry.
Did I "embarrass" you?

05:50.674 --> 05:55.010
No. Because I don't know
what you're "doing."

05:55.012 --> 05:56.945
She's just pointing out
that you have a history

05:56.947 --> 05:58.648
of hiding us bumpkins
in the attic

05:58.649 --> 06:00.281
when it's time
to meet the public.

06:00.283 --> 06:01.683
That is not true.

06:01.685 --> 06:02.985
Oh, please.

06:02.986 --> 06:05.221
The last parent-teacher
conference I even heard about

06:05.222 --> 06:07.222
was fifth grade.

06:07.224 --> 06:10.960
That's because
you would never wear underwear.

06:10.961 --> 06:15.330
You'd sit in those little desks,
showing it to the world.

06:16.733 --> 06:19.801
You got straight A's,
didn't you?

06:19.803 --> 06:21.836
Because I studied.

06:21.838 --> 06:24.039
We'll never know.

06:30.881 --> 06:34.316
Boy, those wasps really
got me good, huh?

06:34.317 --> 06:37.018
Well, at least I'll have a fun
story to tell at your party.

06:37.020 --> 06:39.587
Oh, maybe you shouldn't
tell that one.

06:39.589 --> 06:40.922
Why not?

06:40.924 --> 06:44.126
Mike, you got your ass kicked
by a bunch of wasps.

06:44.127 --> 06:45.361
I know. That's why it's funny.

06:45.362 --> 06:47.329
Besides, you know,
you get beat fair and square,

06:47.330 --> 06:49.230
you got to tip your hat
to the victor.

06:49.232 --> 06:52.000
Yeah, but are they laughing
with you or...

06:52.002 --> 06:54.303
Hey, laughing's laughing.
And they're gonna love the part

06:54.304 --> 06:56.672
where I Aqua Netted
Vince's eyelashes shut.

06:56.673 --> 06:58.374
(laughs)

06:58.375 --> 06:59.975
I wish I could've seen that.

06:59.976 --> 07:01.110
Yeah, so does Vince.

07:01.111 --> 07:02.678
(both laugh)

07:02.679 --> 07:04.180
Oh, yeah...

07:04.181 --> 07:06.382
You know what? I-I don't think
this is gonna be the...

07:06.383 --> 07:09.217
the kind of party where people
are telling stories and...

07:09.219 --> 07:12.221
I thought it was a party for
up-and-coming storytellers.

07:12.222 --> 07:13.723
It is, it is.

07:13.724 --> 07:15.324
But, you know, that's their job.

07:15.325 --> 07:18.327
They're off the clock.
Let's give 'em the night off.

07:18.328 --> 07:20.596
Well, I gotta talk
about something. Do you?

07:20.597 --> 07:21.896
What?
What?

07:21.898 --> 07:22.932
No,

07:22.933 --> 07:23.866
I'm-I'm just saying,

07:23.867 --> 07:25.468
these people are
so full of themselves,

07:25.469 --> 07:26.769
they're gonna do
most of the talking.

07:26.770 --> 07:28.537
You just have to sit there

07:28.538 --> 07:31.474
and listen and just pretend
to be interested. That's it.

07:31.475 --> 07:33.609
It's easy. I do it
with her all the time.

07:33.610 --> 07:34.844
Ma.

07:34.845 --> 07:36.412
No, she's-she's not wrong.

07:36.413 --> 07:37.445
A little mean,

07:37.447 --> 07:38.948
but not wrong.

07:38.949 --> 07:40.115
You know,

07:40.117 --> 07:41.283
these people just...

07:41.284 --> 07:42.818
they're always trying
to one-up you.

07:42.819 --> 07:44.886
It's not a conversation.
It's a competition.

07:44.888 --> 07:46.322
I got you.

07:46.323 --> 07:48.457
It's like when Carl starts
talking about R & B music.

07:48.458 --> 07:49.592
You know what I do?

07:49.593 --> 07:51.827
I rub my nose,
hinting that he has a booger.

07:51.828 --> 07:53.596
Then that's all
he can think about.

07:53.597 --> 07:55.564
Yeah, and then instead of
going on and on

07:55.565 --> 07:58.066
about Marvin Gaye's dad,
he's running for a napkin.

07:59.336 --> 08:00.469
Yeah, I... I don't know

08:00.470 --> 08:02.338
that these are
the types of people

08:02.339 --> 08:05.908
that you're gonna throw off
with a phantom booger.

08:05.909 --> 08:07.109
You know?

08:07.110 --> 08:09.111
They'll just assume
you have one.

08:09.112 --> 08:11.380
Which you kind of do,
by the way.

08:11.381 --> 08:12.715
Nah, that's just a big hair.

08:12.716 --> 08:15.651
I'll yank it in the parking
lot when we get there.

08:15.652 --> 08:17.352
Oh!

08:18.789 --> 08:20.955
Thanks, Ma.

08:27.831 --> 08:30.031
(quiet conversations)

08:31.935 --> 08:32.967
Oh.

08:32.969 --> 08:35.471
Uh, no railing.

08:35.472 --> 08:37.304
Very... very chic.

08:38.375 --> 08:40.142
There's no way this meets code.

08:40.143 --> 08:41.910
Ma, hold my arm.
I'm fine.

08:41.912 --> 08:43.445
Not for you; for me.

08:43.446 --> 08:46.080
This place is beautiful.

08:46.082 --> 08:47.883
You think they got
the game on somewhere?

08:47.884 --> 08:50.085
Mike, these kinds of people
don't watch television.

08:50.086 --> 08:52.187
If they ask, neither do we.

08:52.189 --> 08:53.455
How about a fish tank?

08:53.456 --> 08:55.257
Anything to look at?

08:55.258 --> 08:56.525
Well, this has been fun.

08:56.526 --> 08:58.393
Ready to go?
No.

08:58.395 --> 09:01.096
We gotta stick around until
the new author announcements.

09:01.097 --> 09:02.931
That's the whole reason we came.

09:02.933 --> 09:05.034
Fine. I got to get
a few drinks in me

09:05.035 --> 09:06.569
if they're gonna
parade me up and down

09:06.570 --> 09:08.503
like a shih tzu at a dog show.

09:10.640 --> 09:13.541
I think that statue just moved.

09:13.543 --> 09:15.544
That's because
it's a real person.

09:15.545 --> 09:17.513
No! Are you serious?

09:17.514 --> 09:18.747
Mike, leave him alone.

09:18.748 --> 09:20.683
Remember the robot cowboy
in the park?

09:20.684 --> 09:23.818
You kept blowing in his ear...
he didn't like it.

09:23.820 --> 09:25.621
Well, if you can't
stay in character,

09:25.622 --> 09:27.656
don't paint yourself silver.

09:27.657 --> 09:30.659
Oh, my God, I think
that's Jean Thompson.

09:30.660 --> 09:32.528
She wrote <i>The Year We Left Home.</i>

09:32.529 --> 09:35.130
Well, this will be the year
that I don't read that.

09:35.131 --> 09:36.298
She's coming this way.

09:36.299 --> 09:37.866
Maybe you should go
find your mother.

09:37.868 --> 09:38.968
All right, fine,
but I'll come back

09:38.969 --> 09:40.001
and rescue you if
she's as boring...

09:40.003 --> 09:41.170
Yeah, yeah, yeah, fine,
fine, fine.

09:41.171 --> 09:42.271
All right.

09:42.272 --> 09:43.972
(chuckles)

