09:52.282 --> 09:54.148
(exhales sharply)

09:55.018 --> 09:56.985
You're good.

09:59.022 --> 10:01.557
Not so fast.
What have we got here?

10:01.558 --> 10:03.025
Baked crab on wontons.

10:03.026 --> 10:04.326
Mmm. (chuckles)

10:04.327 --> 10:05.460
(loud crunch)

10:05.462 --> 10:07.229
(gags)

10:07.230 --> 10:10.732
Why didn't you tell me
it was real crab?

10:11.935 --> 10:13.402
Oh, what do we have here?

10:13.403 --> 10:16.605
Real crab.
All right, keep it moving.

10:16.606 --> 10:18.607
So this is your new crowd,
huh, Ma?

10:18.608 --> 10:21.443
You kidding? I'm only
here because I have to.

10:21.444 --> 10:24.380
I got nothing in common
with these poseurs,

10:24.381 --> 10:26.247
kissing each other's asses.

10:26.249 --> 10:27.716
Wait a minute.

10:27.717 --> 10:29.151
I think that's the lady

10:29.152 --> 10:31.287
who wrote <i> Crock-Pot
Confidential.</i>

10:31.288 --> 10:33.622
Oh, is that where you got
that tamale casserole recipe?

10:33.623 --> 10:36.057
Yep, yep, yep.
Bye, bye, bye.

10:41.564 --> 10:44.466
See, I didn't find the piece
so much about desolation

10:44.467 --> 10:46.267
as loneliness.
Mm-hmm.

10:46.269 --> 10:49.037
(crunches) I...

10:49.039 --> 10:51.407
I mean, what I...
what I was saying is that, uh,

10:51.408 --> 10:54.343
underneath it all,
it's really just a-a sobering

10:54.344 --> 10:57.246
account of the human condition.

10:57.247 --> 10:58.246
What is?

10:58.248 --> 10:59.982
We were just discussing

10:59.983 --> 11:02.584
her powerful short story.

11:02.585 --> 11:03.852
Oh, I love short stories!

11:03.853 --> 11:04.987
Better yet...
a minute mystery.

11:04.988 --> 11:06.855
Any of you guys ever
write one of those?

11:06.856 --> 11:08.290
I mean, I know I'm a cop,

11:08.291 --> 11:11.125
but I'm always surprised
by who did it.

11:11.127 --> 11:13.462
Ah, you are such a stitch!

11:13.463 --> 11:14.663
(both chuckle)

11:14.664 --> 11:16.097
Is this your husband?

11:16.099 --> 11:18.767
(quietly): Mm-hmm.

11:18.768 --> 11:20.635
Hey! Mike Biggs.

11:20.637 --> 11:22.871
Nice to meet you.
By the way, if you guys

11:22.872 --> 11:26.107
like mini-hamburgers,
highly recommended.

11:26.109 --> 11:28.309
Kind of in the middle
of a conversation.

11:28.311 --> 11:30.112
Well, if you eat
one of these babies,

11:30.113 --> 11:32.447
that's all you're
gonna be talking about.

11:32.449 --> 11:35.384
Anyway, uh, as I was saying,

11:35.385 --> 11:37.820
I-I really, um... uh...

11:37.821 --> 11:40.622
it... I think sometimes...
(groans, laughs)

11:40.623 --> 11:42.925
Now I don't remember
what I was talking about.

11:42.926 --> 11:45.326
We're talking
about these burgers.

11:45.328 --> 11:46.795
No, you were talking
about the burgers.

11:46.796 --> 11:48.364
We were talking about her...

11:48.365 --> 11:50.666
powerful and moving short story.

11:50.667 --> 11:52.100
MIKE: Hey, I got a story.

11:52.102 --> 11:53.469
Any of you guys
ever go toe-to-toe

11:53.470 --> 11:54.937
with a porch full of wasps, huh?

11:54.938 --> 11:56.138
You ought to see my back, man.

11:56.139 --> 11:57.338
It's like a strip
of bubble wrap.

11:57.340 --> 11:58.907
Goes all the way to here.

11:58.908 --> 12:00.509
Mike! Stop it!

12:00.510 --> 12:02.043
Don't be stupid.

12:03.713 --> 12:05.314
I mean...

12:05.315 --> 12:06.882
I mean silly.

12:06.883 --> 12:08.349
Yeah, I know what you meant.

12:08.351 --> 12:10.219
Mike.

12:10.220 --> 12:11.552
Excuse me.

12:11.554 --> 12:13.489
You were saying about my story?

12:13.490 --> 12:15.690
I don't know.
I didn't read it.

12:27.128 --> 12:28.562
Here.

12:28.563 --> 12:29.897
What's this?
It's the valet ticket.

12:29.898 --> 12:31.365
You and Molly take the car.

12:31.366 --> 12:32.466
I'm heading out.

12:32.467 --> 12:33.667
Oh! There you are.

12:33.668 --> 12:35.469
Yeah, I'm just leaving.

12:35.470 --> 12:37.171
Oh, come on.
Look.

12:37.172 --> 12:38.305
You don't want me here.

12:38.306 --> 12:39.473
I've already
embarrassed you enough.

12:39.474 --> 12:41.442
Just enjoy your party.

12:41.443 --> 12:44.078
But we're good, right?

12:44.079 --> 12:45.379
He'll be fine.

12:45.380 --> 12:47.081
By the way,
don't bother poking her ass.

12:47.082 --> 12:49.148
She's real.

12:53.121 --> 12:55.389
Yeah, and it was
a real snobby party, too.

12:55.390 --> 12:57.057
Real crab, fake people.

12:57.058 --> 12:59.026
I prefer it
the other way around.

12:59.027 --> 13:00.628
And Molly was putting
on airs like...

13:00.629 --> 13:02.463
like she was buying
into the whole thing.

13:02.464 --> 13:06.000
If it was just us, she would've
been making fun of it, too.

13:06.001 --> 13:09.915
See, I just can't believe
she called you stupid.

13:09.916 --> 13:11.049
Bossy.

13:11.051 --> 13:12.051
Blowhard.

13:12.052 --> 13:13.451
Cheap.
Moody.

13:13.453 --> 13:16.488
But not stupid, okay?

13:16.489 --> 13:19.658
Molly's got to understand
that words hurt.

13:19.659 --> 13:22.126
Thanks. You guys are
really cheering me up.

13:22.128 --> 13:24.362
And sarcastic!
That's another one that you are.

13:30.136 --> 13:32.171
Just giving you a heads-up.

13:32.172 --> 13:34.340
I might be writing
a book on cabbage

13:34.341 --> 13:36.108
with that Crock-Pot lady.

13:36.109 --> 13:37.776
I'll honor our deal first.

13:37.777 --> 13:40.446
I just wanted to put it
out in the open.

13:40.447 --> 13:43.549
Okay, for the record,
I did not say he was stupid.

13:43.550 --> 13:45.416
I was saying don't <i> be</i> stupid.

13:45.418 --> 13:47.152
Big difference.

13:47.153 --> 13:48.387
One is being mean,

13:48.388 --> 13:51.890
and the other is keeping him
from being stupid.

13:51.892 --> 13:53.259
So, it was him
you were worried about?

13:53.260 --> 13:54.393
Yes.

13:54.394 --> 13:57.061
What a good wife you are.

13:57.063 --> 13:59.632
I'm sorry, but those people
out there are judging us

13:59.633 --> 14:02.267
on every word we say
and every move we make.

14:02.269 --> 14:03.936
What do you care
what they think?

14:03.937 --> 14:06.772
Because this is part of the
world we live in now, Peggy...

14:06.773 --> 14:09.241
Chicago's literary elite...
and if we want to be successful,

14:09.242 --> 14:11.276
we better play the game.

14:11.278 --> 14:12.645
You play, I'll watch.

14:12.646 --> 14:13.645
Fine!

14:13.647 --> 14:15.047
This is a party
for up-and-comers?

14:15.048 --> 14:17.048
Well, here I come.

14:17.884 --> 14:19.918
Molly?

14:19.920 --> 14:20.953
What?

14:20.954 --> 14:22.655
Go get 'em.

14:22.656 --> 14:24.589
Thank you.

14:29.796 --> 14:31.430
All right,
this is the final question

14:31.431 --> 14:32.665
of the round, gentlemen.

14:32.666 --> 14:35.367
This deadly Twin is
their all-time home run leader.

14:35.368 --> 14:37.902
Harmon Killebrew...
573 home runs.

14:37.904 --> 14:39.305
(dings)

14:39.306 --> 14:40.706
(both grunt)

14:40.707 --> 14:41.941
That is correct!

14:41.942 --> 14:44.642
See? That big head isn't
just for big hats.

14:44.644 --> 14:45.911
(laughs)

14:45.912 --> 14:47.780
Yeah, I might not know
about books or art,

14:47.781 --> 14:49.848
but I can name
every Cub since 1954.

14:49.849 --> 14:52.117
I can also rebuild
any American-made car.

14:52.118 --> 14:54.153
And I can quote
practically every line

14:54.154 --> 14:56.521
Al Pacino has ever said on film.

14:56.523 --> 14:57.989
What about <i> Serpico?</i>

14:57.991 --> 15:00.592
"I'm a marked man
in this department."

15:00.593 --> 15:02.293
(all laugh)

15:02.295 --> 15:04.663
I've never seen it,
but I'm sure that's right.

15:04.664 --> 15:06.097
Yeah!

15:08.435 --> 15:09.468
Hey.

15:09.469 --> 15:11.736
Hey!
Hey!

15:14.975 --> 15:16.141
Hey!

15:16.142 --> 15:18.309
Hello.

15:19.980 --> 15:21.447
Can we talk?

15:21.448 --> 15:23.682
Go ahead, but just so you
know, we're in the middle

15:23.683 --> 15:26.385
of a pretty heated trivia game,
and-and believe it or not,

15:26.386 --> 15:28.219
I'm the brains of the group.

15:28.221 --> 15:30.088
Well, it doesn't surprise me.

15:30.090 --> 15:31.622
It shocked the hell out of us.

15:34.427 --> 15:36.595
You didn't think I was
too smart at that party.

15:36.596 --> 15:39.098
Oh, I wasn't too sure
of anything at that party.

15:39.099 --> 15:42.234
And after you left, it took
a pretty humiliating turn.

15:42.235 --> 15:45.536
And that's before I fell
off the stairs on the way out.

15:47.807 --> 15:50.108
At least the stairs
didn't call you stupid.

15:50.110 --> 15:52.510
No, but the statue did
when I knocked him over.

15:55.448 --> 15:57.582
Those guys have no
sense of humor.

15:58.518 --> 16:00.819
I'm sorry!
I-I was an idiot.

16:00.820 --> 16:03.622
And I just got nervous and
intimidated with those people.

16:03.623 --> 16:05.823
And I put it all on you.

16:05.825 --> 16:07.459
I get it.

16:07.460 --> 16:09.261
You forgive me?
On one condition.

16:09.262 --> 16:10.361
Anything.

16:10.363 --> 16:11.497
Can you join our trivia team?

16:11.498 --> 16:13.465
We're getting
our asses handed to us!

16:13.466 --> 16:15.534
Like I said...
I'm the smart one of the group.

16:15.535 --> 16:18.670
Hey, that's because
my category has not come up yet.

16:18.671 --> 16:20.739
Okay, uh, my area
of expertise is music.

16:20.740 --> 16:22.141
Specifically R & B.

16:22.142 --> 16:23.909
Did you know
that Marvin Gaye's father

16:23.910 --> 16:25.943
was an ordained minister
but never loved his son?

16:25.945 --> 16:28.246
Hmm? And you know...

16:28.248 --> 16:31.049
"Sit... Sittin' on..."

16:32.519 --> 16:34.453
"Sittin' on...
Sitti'' on the Dock of the...

16:34.454 --> 16:36.654
the Dock..." Excuse me.

16:39.159 --> 16:42.094
Hey, that works like a charm.

16:42.095 --> 16:44.362
Every time.

16:44.364 --> 16:46.431
(mutters quietly)

16:48.168 --> 16:49.168
Nah, I'm just kidding.

16:49.169 --> 16:51.402
Oh!
(laughs)

17:01.182 --> 17:02.615
Another party.

17:02.616 --> 17:04.983
Are you sure you want
me to go to this one?

17:04.984 --> 17:06.286
I am big. I am oafy.

17:06.287 --> 17:07.487
I like mini-hamburgers.

17:07.488 --> 17:09.455
And I like talking
about them even more.

17:09.457 --> 17:10.924
You can't embarrass me.

17:10.925 --> 17:12.625
I don't care
what those people think.

17:12.626 --> 17:15.428
Well, you should know
I'm planning on uncorking

17:15.429 --> 17:17.363
some new jokes
that I heard at work,

17:17.364 --> 17:18.998
and the ones
that aren't toilet-based...

17:18.999 --> 17:21.634
real dirty.

17:21.635 --> 17:23.936
Mike, you're going
to this party.

17:23.938 --> 17:26.205
Damn it. It was a lot easier
to get out of these things

17:26.207 --> 17:27.705
when you were ashamed of me.

17:27.708 --> 17:29.809
Look, I know this party
is gonna be horrible,

17:29.810 --> 17:33.580
but I wouldn't want to share
my misery with anybody but you.

17:33.581 --> 17:35.448
That's sweet.

17:35.449 --> 17:38.217
Oh, by the way, save Saturday
night for Carl's birthday.

17:38.219 --> 17:39.619
We're gonna watch
all three <i> Godfathers.</i>

17:39.620 --> 17:43.021
I'm gonna karaoke all
of Al Pacino's lines.

17:44.158 --> 17:46.726
You don't have to go tonight.

17:46.727 --> 17:48.394
Hoo-ha!

17:48.395 --> 17:49.895
Stupid like a fox!

